  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6582.7 sitting between the max negative gamma at 6500 (-4.5B) and max positive gamma at 6600 (+3.8B), dealers are currently in neutral hedging mode but poised for aggressive buying if we break toward 6500. The PIN regime with 1.1B total GEX suggests dealers will fade any move - selling rallies toward the 6600-6605 resistance wall and buying aggressively into any weakness toward the 6500 support level. The recent GEX surge combined with the massive negative gamma below current levels creates a asymmetric setup where downside breaks accelerate but upside is capped by dealer selling.\n\nKey levels: 6500 (major dealer buying), 6600 (dealer selling resistance), and 6808 flip line where regime changes.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect price to get pinned between 6500-6600 with dealers providing strong support at 6500.",
